abstract: A lawyer for more than 200 women and girls who accused Mr. Nassar of abuse called the offer “unconscionable.”
snippet: A lawyer for more than 200 women and girls who accused Mr. Nassar of abuse called the offer “unconscionable.”
lead_paragraph: U.S.A. Gymnastics on Thursday offered to pay $215 million to settle legal claims brought by athletes who say they were sexually abused by Lawrence G. Nassar, the disgraced former national team doctor.

abstract: The former senator John Warner issued a statement Thursday night calling on his fellow Republicans to bring “relevant witnesses and documents.”
snippet: The former senator John Warner issued a statement Thursday night calling on his fellow Republicans to bring “relevant witnesses and documents.”
lead_paragraph: John Warner, a Republican elder statesman who served for 30 years in the Senate, called on his fellow Republicans on Thursday night to bring “relevant witnesses and documents” into President Trump’s impeachment trial.
headline_main: Former senator calls on Republicans to allow witnesses.

abstract: Internal emails show that Federal Reserve leaders emailed around an article in which a Republican senator defended the chair.
snippet: Internal emails show that Federal Reserve leaders emailed around an article in which a Republican senator defended the chair.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s nonstop attacks on the Federal Reserve have raised eyebrows and broken with recent presidential norms. But an Aug. 23 tweet in which Mr. Trump called the Fed chair, Jerome H. Powell, an “enemy” of America appears to have prompted some hand-wringing inside the central bank.

abstract: The Federal Communications Commission said the intent of the robocalls was to “cause harm” with more than 6,000 such calls in six states.
snippet: The Federal Communications Commission said the intent of the robocalls was to “cause harm” with more than 6,000 such calls in six states.
lead_paragraph: A man who telecom regulators say was apparently behind a barrage of racist robocalls in six states — sowing hate in response to the killing of an Iowa college student by an undocumented immigrant and a white supremacist’s murder trial in Virginia  — is facing a proposed fine of nearly $13 million by the Federal Communications Commission.

abstract: Senator Lisa Murkowski of Alaska is a critical swing vote on the question of whether to compel more witnesses or documents.
snippet: Senator Lisa Murkowski of Alaska is a critical swing vote on the question of whether to compel more witnesses or documents.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lisa Murkowski, Republican of Alaska, who is weighing whether to join Democrats in voting to hear witnesses in President Trump’s impeachment trial, may have tipped her hand Thursday evening with a pointed question for Mr. Trump’s defense team: “Why should this body not call Ambassador Bolton?”

abstract: An end to President Donald Trump's impeachment trial appears closer after one influential Republican senator said he would not support a call for more witness.
snippet: An end to President Donald Trump's impeachment trial appears closer after one influential Republican senator said he would not support a call for more witness.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An end to President Donald Trump's impeachment trial appears closer after one influential Republican senator said he would not support a call for more witness.
headline_main: Trial Highlights: Alexander Decides, Dershowitz Backtracks
headline_print_headline: Trial Highlights: Alexander Decides, Dershowitz Backtracks

abstract: Attention has centered on four Republicans who might break ranks in President Trump’s impeachment trial. But Democrats have their own list of potential defectors.
snippet: Attention has centered on four Republicans who might break ranks in President Trump’s impeachment trial. But Democrats have their own list of potential defectors.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nothing would please President Trump more than to wrap up his impeachment trial with support from a handful of Democrats. He might get his wish.

abstract: Andrew Yang is showing what healthy populism looks like.
snippet: Andrew Yang is showing what healthy populism looks like.
lead_paragraph: It was New Year’s Eve, and I had decided to spend it with Andrew Yang. A self-described “Asian man who’s good at math,” Mr. Yang had raised an impressive $16.5 million in the fourth quarter of 2019 for his presidential campaign. Despite being newly flush, the campaign didn’t hold its shindig in a Napa Valley wine cave or at Gramercy Tavern, but in a fluorescent-lit room above a bar in Nashua, N.H.
